WHEREAS, Provider has developed and owns certain technology in the field of {{technology_field}};

WHEREAS, Recipient desires to obtain rights to such technology for commercialization{{#if field_of_use}} in the field of {{field_of_use}}{{/if}};

WHEREAS, Provider is willing to transfer such technology and provide associated know-how and support;

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained herein, the Parties agree as follows:

2. TECHNOLOGY TRANSFER

2.1 Grant of Rights. Provider hereby {{#if assignment}}assigns{{else}}grants to Recipient {{#if exclusive}}an exclusive{{else}}a non-exclusive{{/if}} license to{{/if}} the Technology{{#if field_of_use}} in the Field of Use{{/if}} in the Territory.

2.2 Delivery. Provider shall deliver to Recipient within [30] days:
(a) All documentation related to the Technology;
(b) {{#if software}}Source code and technical documentation;{{/if}}
(c) {{#if materials}}Physical materials and samples;{{/if}}
(d) Know-How in written and electronic form.

2.3 Transfer Method. Delivery shall be made via [secure file transfer/physical shipment] with appropriate confidentiality protections.

4. FINANCIAL TERMS

4.1 Technology Transfer Fee. Recipient shall pay Provider ${{number upfront_fee}} within thirty (30) days of the Effective Date.

{{#if milestone_payments}}4.2 Milestone Payments. Recipient shall pay the following milestone payments:
(a) $[AMOUNT] upon [MILESTONE 1];
(b) $[AMOUNT] upon [MILESTONE 2];
(c) $[AMOUNT] upon [MILESTONE 3].{{/if}}

{{#if royalties}}4.3 Royalties. Recipient shall pay Provider {{royalty_rate}}% of Net Sales of products incorporating the Technology.{{/if}}

4.4 Payment Terms. All payments shall be made in US dollars via wire transfer. Late payments bear interest at 1.5% per month.

6. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY

6.1 Ownership. {{#if assignment}}All rights in the Technology transfer to Recipient upon payment of the Technology Transfer Fee.{{else}}Provider retains all ownership rights in the Technology.{{/if}}

6.2 Improvements. {{#if exclusive}}Recipient owns all improvements made to the Technology. Provider receives a non-exclusive license back.{{else}}Each Party owns its improvements, with cross-licenses granted.{{/if}}

6.3 No Other Rights. No other intellectual property rights are granted except as expressly stated herein.

7. CONFIDENTIALITY

7.1 Obligations. Each Party shall maintain the other's Confidential Information in strict confidence for {{confidentiality_period}} years.

7.2 Exceptions. Obligations do not apply to information that:
(a) Is publicly available;
(b) Was rightfully known before disclosure;
(c) Is independently developed;
(d) Must be disclosed by law.

7.3 Return. Upon termination, each Party shall return or destroy all Confidential Information.
